**Analysis of the Main Target Image**

1. **Overall Count and Layers**

   - The structure naturally divides into two separate assemblies:

     • **Left “Tower” (7 blocks total)**  
       1× Yellow rectangular base  
       2× Orange cylinders (stacked vertically)  
       1× Yellow rectangular block bridging across the cylinders  
       1× Red arch block on top of that  
       1× Red cube above the arch  
       1× Orange wedge‐shaped “roof”  

     • **Right “Arch Complex” (12 blocks total)**  
       2× Red arch blocks at the front base (side by side)  
       3× Orange rectangular blocks (one atop each arch and one toward the right/rear)  
       2× Yellow half‐cylinders (side by side, curved side up)  
       2× Green vertical rectangular blocks behind the arches  
       1× Blue cube behind/next to the left arch  
       2× Tall yellow rectangular blocks at the rear (the “towers”)  

   - **Total Blocks**: 7 (left) + 12 (right) = 19 blocks  
   - **Layering**:  
     • The left tower is essentially a straight vertical stack from bottom (yellow rectangle) upward to the orange wedge roof.  
     • The right structure has a front row of red arches, a second row of half‐cylinders and orange blocks, then green and blue blocks behind, and finally two tall yellow blocks at the back.

2. **Required Blocks From the Dictionary (Indices & Quantities)**

   Below are the dictionary‐index matches, **exactly** as shown (no rotation beyond what is pictured):

   • **Left Tower**  
     - #8 (Yellow rectangular block) – used twice  
     - #10 (Orange cylinder) – used twice  
     - #1 (Red arch block) – used once  
     - #5 (Red cube) – used once  
     - #16 (Orange wedge) – used once  

   • **Right Arch Complex**  
     - #1 (Red arch block) – used twice  
     - #14 (Orange rectangular block) – used three times  
     - #11 (Yellow half‐cylinder) – used twice  
     - #6 (Green vertical rectangular block) – used twice  
     - #3 (Blue cube) – used once  
     - #9 (Tall yellow rectangular block) – used twice
